page.title: 08Brunswick Village.
page.content: {Brunswick village}is in the North-East corner of our twelve square miles we had to survey. Brunswick village is divided in two by the{A1}which runs from North to South. On the west side of the A1 there are a few public services. On Grey Street there were two hairdressers, a newsagents and a post office. All of these shops were converted from old terraced houses. In Darrel Street there is Brunswick Beech school for infants and a butchers, opposite there is a church and a{Spar.}Near to the Spar is Sacred Heart{primary school. We surveyed the opposite side of the motorway finding information. On Cantabury Way there was Wide Open public library, there was also a school, Woodlands first school which was joined to Woodlands Park health centre.
